Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of the expected end-to-end bit error rate (BER) values for network coded systems, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on cooperative communication and network coding, which are important topics in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a network decoder with reduced complexity, which is a control system design problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance analysis of network coded systems under quasi-static Rayleigh fading channels, which is relevant to multimedia communication. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the design and optimization of communication systems in various societal contexts.
